title.narrative: ACCESS TO CHILD HEALTH SERVICES

description.narrative: By 2018, access to services for the prevention and control of priority communicable diseases improved, which contributes to Adolescent Health And Nutrition, Immunization. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By the end of 2018, 85% of mothers, adolescents, newborns and under-fives, especially the most vulnerable, benefit from access to health care services, including HIV prevention, care, treatment and support.

description.narrative: UNICEF supported immunization acceleration activities in chronically low performing districts by implementing an equity-based micro-planning carried out by health facilities to reduce drop out rates and improve coverage of remote and poor rural communities.
